Description: The warm, rich color and timeless beauty of Mendocino Redwood creates a breathtaking first impression. Beyond first impressions, it blends into the landscape creating a peaceful and relaxing natural outdoor living environment. With simple care and maintenance, your redwood deck, fence and outdoor living structures will provide decades of excellent performance, and long-lasting value. Mendocino Redwood is one of nature's finest and strongest building materials with shear strength up to five times greater than other decking materials. Whether you're building a deck, fence, play set or outdoor living structure; the enduring strength of redwood means safety and security for those that matter most. Nature can be harsh on outdoor living spaces - but Mendocino Redwood naturally stands up to the elements, insects, decay, warping, and splitting. All while staying comfortable on bare feet even on the hottest, sunniest days. Using energy-efficient natural redwood products helps store carbon instead of energy-intensive manufactured products that release carbon, therefore lowering your carbon footprint and reducing carbon emissions. Whether you are a frequent entertainer, or prefer to relax in the quiet of your own home, decks, fences, landscapes, and garden structures made of real redwood make for a beautiful addition. Mendocino Redwood is a high-quality, long-lasting, eco-friendly building material, which makes it the right choice for outdoor construction projects.
Item Name: Mendocino Forest Products 2 in. x 8 in. x 8 ft. Construction Heart S4S Green Redwood Lumber

Description: Multinautic developed sturdy hardware kits to make it easy for you to build the wood dock of your dreams. Inspired by our challenging customer base of waterfront residents we have designed this Collection of Docks Kits from the most popular sizes. They are composed of our sturdy hot-dipped galvanized steel hardware and the famous foam-filled Eagle Floats, allowing you to choose between medium or high freeboard ensembles to fit your favorite nautical activities. Start your layout with a semi-floating section and connect it to one or more floating kits to meet your needs. In shallow waters connect robust leg docks to reach the semi-floating section or create a complete stationary dock layout. To assess your needs, consider your neighbors' docks. If they have been installed for a few years and are still in good condition, a similar choice may be right for you. Refer to our PLANNING GUIDE available on this page. It could be an L-shaped dock, a straight line to reach deeper water, or a U-shaped dock to securely moor a boat, protected from large waves. From small, easy-to-move dock to large floating sections up to 10 ft. x 16 ft. you'll find what works best for your layout. The possibilities are endless. This new Collection will accommodate family and friends to enjoy summer fun to the fullest. For this 4 ft. x 16 ft. Medium Freeboard Semi-Floating Dock, 19374, the required lumber list to get (from homedepot.com or locally) is detailed in the PDF file to download from this webpage.

Description: With the Multinautic QPF-495 Aluminum Dock Series, it's easy to reach out to your dream of a dock that fits your needs. This simple Collection lets you combine 5 ft. x 10 ft. dock sections in a straight line, side by side or in an "L" shape to adjust to your own design. It's the perfect dock size unit for a light frame assembly that offers a low or a medium freeboard depending on your favorite nautical activities and the specifications of your shoreline. Simply choose Stationary and/or Floating Ensembles with or without Cedar Decking. Each unit is modular, letting you decide of the exact configuration that will suit your precise needs. Combining 3 dock sections or more in a Floating layout will allow mooring up to a 25-ft. long boat. Its sleek and unique designed aluminum frame system allows you to insert your mooring cleats (and other accessories) in the top track, without drilling into your decking, and relocate them where you want. Decking boards can be assembled as panels to be rapidly removed from the sub frame to lighten manipulations seasonally year after year. The included assembly hardware for the frame is all stainless steel or hot dip galvanized. This page presents the 5 ft x 10 ft Aluminum Stationary Dock Kit Model QPF-495 With Cedar Decking, product 21577.

(actual size 1.5 x 3.5 in.) railing bracket, made of hard nylon material, stands out with its excellent weight-bearing capacity, corrosion and wear resistance, capable of withstanding wind and rain for years of both indoor and outdoor use. Compared to metal, it is more cost-effective and an ideal choice for building new railings. The bracket is compatible with standard-sized wood and suitable for connecting wooden parts such as wood deck railings, wooden fences, wooden handrails, porch railings, etc. and it's easy to fit slightly larger wood through sanding. The package includes 20 black railing brackets and 120 rust-proof nickel-plated screws. Installation is simple and quick, requiring no complicated assembly, just a few minutes with a drill to securely connect the wood to the brackets. Additionally, the brackets support multi-angle adjustments from 0-180, making them perfect for DIY projects in the home or garden, giving them a clean and professional look.
